OL,3,C'Science doesn't back it': Doctors
OL,4,Ccall for ban on smacking children in
OL,5,CEngland
OL,7,FAccording to the Children Act 2004, it
OL,8,Fis unlawful to hit your child, except
OL,9,Fwhere it is "reasonable punishment",
OL,10,Fand this is judged on a case-by-case
OL,11,Fbasis.
OL,13,FThe College is now calling for
OL,14,Fpoliticians to support an amendment to
OL,15,Fthe Children's Wellbeing and Schools
OL,16,FBill that would remove the "reasonable
OL,17,Fpunishment" defence from law in
OL,18,FEngland.
