OL,3,C'Science doesn't back it': Doctors
OL,4,Ccall for ban on smacking children in
OL,5,CEngland
OL,7,FProfessor Andrew Rowland, a consultant
OL,8,Fpaediatrician and RCPCH officer for
OL,9,Fchild protection, said: "There is an
OL,10,Famendment for the Children's Wellbeing
OL,11,Fand Schools Bill that we would like to
OL,12,Fsee passed, which would remove the
OL,13,Fdefence of reasonable punishment.
OL,15,F"That defence of reasonable punishment
OL,16,Fof children in England has been around
OL,17,Fsince 1860 but, in recent legislation,
OL,18,Fit was introduced in the Children Act
OL,19,Fof 2004.
